            <p>2127 Gratz Avenue<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia&#44; July the 27&#44; 1896<lb/></p>
            <p>The Rev. Dr. Sabato Morais&#44;<lb/>
                My Dear and honored Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Your telegram has reached me.  I did not deem it necessary to reply by wire&#44; it<lb/> being understood that I am only too willing and much honored to be your substi&#45;<lb/>tute in any office or function you may choose to command my services.&#45;&#45;My wife<lb/> joins me in praying that you may be greatly benefited by your stay in a saline<lb/> atmosphere.  May the gracious Father in heaven lengthen and sweeten your years&#44;<lb/> whose life has been a continuous blessing for all those who delight to walk in<lb/> the light of God&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>Your most loyal friend<lb/>
                Henry Iliowizi<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
